    "kind": "result",
    "statement": "Adding lorentz(x) = 1/sqrt(1-x\u00b2) as a compound unary operator with a simplification rule that rewrites div(X, sqrt(sub(1, square(Y)))) \u2192 mul(X, lorentz(Y)) reduces total node count by 12 across 4 relativistic equations while maintaining 50/50 exact matches.",
